rtItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532290\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532290\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tcu1665702530867.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tcu1665702530867.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tcu1665702530867.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"tcu1665702530867\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Data Types\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__data_types_136211\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Data types are classifications for data containers, such as fields, variables, parameters, and return values. They define the characteristics of the data and determine how the data is handled during processing and storage.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__p_d44297e1_d44298e1_d44299e1\">Each database and programming language, including Uniface ProcScript, has its own data type definitions. Uniface uses mappings, known as packing codes, to map Uniface scalar data types to DBMS-specific data types (known as <dfn class=\"term\">storage formats</dfn>).</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__topic_d28587e1_d28588e1_d28589e1_d28590e1_d28591e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d853501e59\">\n                  \n DBMS Data Types\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__p_d44303e1_d44304e1_d44305e1\">Most DBMS manufacturers use the term <dfn class=\"term\">data type</dfn> to describe the different types of data storage format which they support. Data types such as Char, Number, and Date are very DBMS-specific because:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__li_d22130e1_d22131e1_d22132e1\">Different DBMS vendors can use different names for the same data types, or the same name for different data types.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__li_d22133e1_d22134e1_d22135e1\">Some DBMSs do not support all the data types available in Uniface.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__li_d22136e1_d22137e1_d22138e1\">Different DBMS vendors can implement the actual storage of the same data types in different ways.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__p_d44306e1_d44307e1_d44308e1\">For example, a Date data type in Sybase is called Datetime, and a Date data type in ORACLE is called Date. Sybase stores dates as 8-byte combined Date and Time fields, comprising a 4-byte time integer and a 4-byte date integer, measuring the number of days and the time of day since January 1, 1900. ORACLE stores dates as combined Datetime fields in the format <var class=\"keyword varname\">dd-mm-yy hh:nn</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">AM</code> (or <code class=\"ph codeph\">PM</code>).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__topic_d28592e1_d28593e1_d28594e1_d28595e1_d28596e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d853501e95\">\n                  \n Uniface Scalar Data Types\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__p_d44312e1_d44313e1_d44314e1\">Uniface scalar data types are matched to storage formats via packing codes. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wop1665702530947.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wop1665702530947.html\" title=\"DBMS vendors use the term data type to describe the way data is handled and stored on disk, but this invariably means the way the data is actually stored. In Uniface documentation, the term storage format is therefore used to refer to DBMS data types . A Uniface data type is specified for each field in a modeled entity; a DBMS storage format is internal to the DBMS.\">Storage Formats</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uww1665702531035.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uww1665702531035.html\" title=\"Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines.\">Packing Codes</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Uniface Scalar Data Types</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">Data Type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\"> PackingCode</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Allowed Values</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Remarks</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">boolean</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">B</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">T</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">F</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> or\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jmt1665702530694.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jmt1665702530694.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a Boolean value of 0 or 1.\">boolean</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">date</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">D</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Integer representing a date in the format\n\t\t\t\t <var class=\"keyword varname\">ccyymmdd</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aon1665702531769.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aon1665702531769.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a sequence of numbers representing a date, in the format ccyymmdd.\">date</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">datetime</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">E</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Integer representing a date and time in\n\t\t\t\t the format <var class=\"keyword varname\">ccyymmddhhnnss</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Combined date and Time. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qpi1665702757314.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qpi1665702757314.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a sequence of numbers representing a date and time, in the format ccyymmddhhnnsstt.\">datetime</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">float</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">F</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Number with a floating decimal point</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Floating decimal point to allow high\n\t\t\t\t precision data and calculations. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fyf1665702757387.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fyf1665702757387.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a number with a floating decimal point.\">float</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">image</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">I</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Binary data for an image</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"arf1665702757675.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/arf1665702757675.html\" title=\"Uniface data type containing binary data.\">image</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">lineardate</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">LD</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Integer from <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> through\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">3652425</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Linear Date represents a number of days.\nFor more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rsb1665702757952.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rsb1665702757952.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds an integer representing a number of days.\">lineardate</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">lineardatetime</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">LE</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Number from <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> through\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">10000</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Linear Date and Time represents a number\n\t\t\t\t of days. Partial days (hours, minutes, seconds) can be expressed as a fraction of a day.\nFor more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oyc1665702758021.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oyc1665702758021.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that represents a number of days, including fractions of days.\">lineardatetime</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">lineartime</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">LT</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Integer from <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> through\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">24</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">Linear Time represents a number of hours. For more information, see \n\t\t\t\t <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mwa1665702758092.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mwa1665702758092.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds an integer that represents a number of hours.\">lineartime</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">numeric</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">N</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Number to a maximum of 9 decimal places,\n                     including <code class=\"ph codeph\">+</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">-</code>, and decimal point\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">.</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yeo1699862389212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yeo1699862389212.html\" title=\"Uniface data type specifying a number to a maximum of 38 decimal places, including +, -, and decimal point .\">numeric</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">raw</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">R</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Binary data</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qms1665702670332.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qms1665702670332.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds binary data.\">raw</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">string</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">S</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Any characters in the UTF-8 character set,\n\t\t\t\t or an empty string.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ozv1665702676080.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ozv1665702676080.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a sequence of characters that is treated as text.\">string</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">time</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">T</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Integer representing a date in the format\n\t\t\t\t <var class=\"keyword varname\">hhnnss</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n                          For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ike1665702758302.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ike1665702758302.html\" title=\"Uniface data type that holds a sequence of numbers that represent a time, in the format hhnnss.\">time</a>.\n                        </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__1\">xmlstream</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__2\">XM</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__3\">Well-formed XML data</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"tcu1665702530867__table_d4253e1_d4254e1_d4255e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"khm1665702758375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/khm1665702758375.html\" title=\"Uniface data type containing well-formed XML.\">xmlstream</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"tcu1665702530867__p_d44315e1_d44316e1_d44317e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dld1665702530483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dld1665702530483.html\" title=\"Data types are classifications for data containers, such as fields, variables, parameters, and return values. They define the characteristics of the data and determine how the data is handled during processing and storage. Uniface has scalar data types and reference data types.\">Uniface Data Types</a>\n</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wop1665702530947.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Storage Formats</a><p>DBMS vendors use the term data type to describe the way data is handled and stored on disk, but this invariably means the way the data is actually stored. In Uniface documentation, the term storage format is therefore used to refer to DBMS data types . A Uniface data type is specified for each field in a modeled entity; a DBMS storage format is internal to the DBMS.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uww1665702531035.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes</a><p>Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532290\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532290\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Types Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Types Data types are classifications for data containers, such as fields, variables, parameters, and return values. They define the characteristics of the data and determine how the data is handled during processing and storage. Each database and programming language, including Uniface ProcScript, has its own data type definitions. Uniface uses mappings, known as packing codes, to map Uniface scalar data types to DBMS-specific data types (known as storage formats ). DBMS Data Types Most DBMS manufacturers use the term data type to describe the different types of data storage format which they support. Data types such as Char, Number, and Date are very DBMS-specific because: Different DBMS vendors can use different names for the same data types, or the same name for different data types. Some DBMSs do not support all the data types available in Uniface. Different DBMS vendors can implement the actual storage of the same data types in different ways. For example, a Date data type in Sybase is called Datetime, and a Date data type in ORACLE is called Date. Sybase stores dates as 8-byte combined Date and Time fields, comprising a 4-byte time integer and a 4-byte date integer, measuring the number of days and the time of day since January 1, 1900. ORACLE stores dates as combined Datetime fields in the format dd-mm-yy hh:nn AM (or PM ). Uniface Scalar Data Types Uniface scalar data types are matched to storage formats via packing codes. For more information, see Storage Formats and Packing Codes . Table 1. Uniface Scalar Data Types Data Type PackingCode Allowed Values Remarks boolean B T or F , 1 or 0 For more information, see boolean . date D Integer representing a date in the format ccyymmdd For more information, see date . datetime E Integer representing a date and time in the format ccyymmddhhnnss Combined date and Time. For more information, see datetime . float F Number with a floating decimal point Floating decimal point to allow high precision data and calculations. For more information, see float . image I Binary data for an image For more information, see image . lineardate LD Integer from 0 through 3652425 Linear Date represents a number of days. For more information, see lineardate . lineardatetime LE Number from 0 through 10000 Linear Date and Time represents a number of days. Partial days (hours, minutes, seconds) can be expressed as a fraction of a day. For more information, see lineardatetime . lineartime LT Integer from 0 through 24 Linear Time represents a number of hours. For more information, see lineartime . numeric N Number to a maximum of 9 decimal places, including + , - , and decimal point . For more information, see numeric . raw R Binary data For more information, see raw . string S Any characters in the UTF-8 character set, or an empty string. For more information, see string . time T Integer representing a date in the format hhnnss For more information, see time . xmlstream XM Well-formed XML data For more information, see xmlstream . For more information, see Uniface Data Types Related Links Storage Formats DBMS vendors use the term data type to describe the way data is handled and stored on disk, but this invariably means the way the data is actually stored. In Uniface documentation, the term storage format is therefore used to refer to DBMS data types . A Uniface data type is specified for each field in a modeled entity; a DBMS storage format is internal to the DBMS. Packing Codes Packing codes are mappings between Uniface data types and DBMS data types (storage formats). When writing a field, Uniface passes the data and a valid packing code to the DBMS connector, which uses the packing code to determine the appropriate storage format for storing the data in the target DBMS. Packing codes also determine how data is interfaced with 3GL routines. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}